name: Gregory O. Page, DMD

reviews.text: Haven’t been to the dentist in a long time. I must say this was a great experience after not having my teeth checked out in a while. I’m completly satisfied with the work I got done today. The staff is super friendly and very funny. I wasn’t in any kind of pain. And my mouth feels AMAZING!! I read the reviews about Dr. Page and immediately booked an appointment, and I’m glad to be writing an awesome review like the rest on my experience.

Dr. Page is a great dentist.  He treats his patients and his staff as family and or close friends.  His work is clean and at a good pace. He is funny and is honest in regards to the treatment that is needed. He has a great sense of humar and is a people person.  The office is small but welcoming and the environment makes you feel at ease. If you're looking for a good dentis Dr. Page should be on your list.

Maybe I reviewed someplace else! Dr. Page and his office deserve MORE than 5 stars. Years ago, Dr. Page gave me back my smile. I had a baby tooth that was loose for a million years. Then it fell out, leaving me snaggled! (Of course, it was a tooth near the front.) Dr. Page fixed it with a bridge, and I could smile again. He and Simone, the hygienist have helped me keep my mouth in tip top shape. I am grateful.

This is by far my best experience at a dentist's office. I always hated to go to one and most of the time ended up with a bad experience until I was cared for by this dentist. Great dentist, excellent and efficeint work! I ll fly back from Senegal on any given day just to go get my teeths worked on there. Thanks a million! Fatoumata Seck

I have been a patient of Dr Page for about 8 years and I just left his office late this afternoon.  The office is close to major subway lines and there is also a bus stop directly across the street.

The office staff is very professional, courteous and genuinely cares about their patients.  I am always impressed when I visit the office that Dr Page seems to have the latest technology and new dental instruments.  I really like that after my dental cleanings that I am thoroughly examined by Dr Page, himself, and not an assistant.  

His hygienist, Simone, cannot be beat.  She's diligent, thorough and fun, too.  Gone are the days of employees who don't take pride in their work when it comes to this dental practice!  

I would travel further than I do now to go to a dentist who doesn't attempt to "sell you procedures" that really are not required.  Or to go to one who doesn't bill things to  your insurance that weren't done.  Can we say Dr Page is honest?  YES!    

I highly recommend you giving this office your trust and business for you and to your family.  I have visited when children are there.  They are leaving with smiles on their faces.  Obviously, Dr Page and his team know how to calm one's fears!    

Enjoy your visits!
